1
00:01:27,160 --> 00:01:35,020
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,509 --> 00:01:37,800
[Episode 4]

3
00:01:38,950 --> 00:01:39,600
Come on.

4
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:41,210
Look. I braised these myself.

5
00:01:41,210 --> 00:01:43,140
-You're being too kind.
-Go ahead.

6
00:01:43,259 --> 00:01:44,920
That's really too kind of you.

7
00:01:44,950 --> 00:01:45,500
It's my pleasure.

8
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,450
Go ahead and try it.

9
00:01:46,450 --> 00:01:47,450
Thank you so much.

10
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,340
Here. Try some.

11
00:01:48,340 --> 00:01:49,009
-Duck tongue.
-It's okay—

12
00:01:49,009 --> 00:01:49,850
You know the motto

13
00:01:49,850 --> 00:01:50,910
of Wenzhou people?

14
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:52,009
"No matter how poor,
never work for others.

15
00:01:52,009 --> 00:01:52,950
No matter how hungry, never beg for food.

16
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:53,979
We'd rather sleep on the floor

17
00:01:53,979 --> 00:01:55,380
than not be our own boss."

18
00:01:55,450 --> 00:01:56,140
You're young,

19
00:01:56,140 --> 00:01:57,789
always busy and never tired.

20
00:01:58,060 --> 00:01:59,590
You'll definitely make it.

21
00:01:59,789 --> 00:02:00,840
What you just said,

22
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:02,010
could you say that again?

23
00:02:02,010 --> 00:02:03,090
Why would you want to write that down?

24
00:02:03,090 --> 00:02:04,120
I am a screenwriter.

25
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:05,200
When I hear something interesting,

26
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,060
I write it down.

27
00:02:06,060 --> 00:02:06,760
Really? A screenwriter?

28
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,370
He's a screenwriter.

29
00:02:07,370 --> 00:02:08,580
I'm studying to become a singer.

30
00:02:08,580 --> 00:02:09,520
We just arrived in Beijing.

31
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:10,960
We're setting up a stall
to make ends meet.

32
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,560
We're in it for the long haul.

33
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:15,310
Not asking your family for money.
That's great.

34
00:02:15,310 --> 00:02:16,170
Such good kids.

35
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:17,240
I really should

36
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,910
give you some proper advice then.

37
00:02:18,910 --> 00:02:19,650
We Wenzhou people

38
00:02:19,650 --> 00:02:20,970
have our own formula for doing business.

39
00:02:20,970 --> 00:02:22,360
The way you're displaying things now

40
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,340
isn't quite right.

41
00:02:23,340 --> 00:02:24,200
Let me show you.

42
00:02:25,910 --> 00:02:27,100
"If you display it,

43
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:28,120
people will buy it."

44
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,400
You should have them high.

45
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:29,870
Right?

46
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,170
"If you display a lot,

47
00:02:31,170 --> 00:02:32,500
people will check them out.

48
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:33,680
If the goods are neat,

49
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,750
the customers will be pleased.

50
00:02:34,750 --> 00:02:35,960
If the quality is good,

51
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,400
the business will last till you're old."

52
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:37,800
Right?

53
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,280
Makes sense.

54
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:38,930
These here

55
00:02:38,930 --> 00:02:39,840
aren't enough.

56
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:40,780
Not enough to choose from.

57
00:02:40,780 --> 00:02:41,470
Come on, have them out.

58
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:42,340
Put them here.

59
00:02:42,430 --> 00:02:42,910
Okay.

60
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:43,860
Right.

61
00:02:44,620 --> 00:02:45,840
Don't make it too crowded though.

62
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,370
It'll make them look cheap.

63
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:48,700
Look at this one.

64
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:49,590
This is a great brand,

65
00:02:49,590 --> 00:02:51,050
you shouldn't put it here.

66
00:02:51,130 --> 00:02:52,210
Nobody will see it.

67
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:52,840
Let's hang it up.

68
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,750
Yes, hang it up.

69
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,000
Exactly.

70
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,360
What did I just say?

71
00:02:57,530 --> 00:02:58,360
"If you display it,

72
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:58,930
people will buy it."

73
00:02:58,930 --> 00:02:59,590
And?

74
00:02:59,690 --> 00:03:00,890
"If you display a lot,

75
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:02,030
people will check them out."

76
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:02,430
Right.

77
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,870
Here, let me put this up for you.

78
00:03:04,870 --> 00:03:05,410
And also,

79
00:03:05,430 --> 00:03:06,890
the most important thing—

80
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:08,360
you need to hawk your wares.

81
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,870
Which of you two can do that?

82
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:10,180
You?

83
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:11,860
I... I'll do it.

84
00:03:11,930 --> 00:03:12,250
Yeah?

85
00:03:12,250 --> 00:03:13,360
Alright, here we go.

86
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,480
Arm up, hand on hip.

87
00:03:15,430 --> 00:03:17,290
Check this out! Don't miss out!

88
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,579
Louder! Louder!

89
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:20,020
Check this out!

90
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:21,410
Don't miss out!

91
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:22,960
Head up, chest out. Confidence!

92
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:23,690
Confidence!

93
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:24,510
That's it!

94
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:26,210
Check this out! Don't miss out!

95
00:03:26,210 --> 00:03:26,970
Come and take a look!

96
00:03:26,970 --> 00:03:27,410
Good.

97
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,300
How much?

98
00:03:28,370 --> 00:03:29,579
Twenty yuan per piece.

99
00:03:29,579 --> 00:03:30,370
Twenty.

100
00:03:30,430 --> 00:03:31,700
Twenty per piece!

101
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:34,090
Check this out! Don't miss out!

102
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:34,960
Very promising.

103
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,360
You won't get ripped off!

104
00:03:36,590 --> 00:03:37,590
Thank you so much.

105
00:03:38,090 --> 00:03:39,970
We're both from Wenzhou—you're so welcome.

106
00:03:39,970 --> 00:03:41,220
Twenty. It's a bargain.

107
00:03:41,220 --> 00:03:42,650
This is from Guangzhou.

108
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:43,800
A silk blend.

109
00:03:44,370 --> 00:03:45,930
Great quality. Wrinkle-free.

110
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:46,930
-Here comes business.
-You can try it on.

111
00:03:46,930 --> 00:03:47,780
Feel free to try it on.

112
00:03:47,780 --> 00:03:48,710
This looks really nice.

113
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:49,310
Yes!

114
00:03:49,310 --> 00:03:50,620
This one is 20 yuan.

115
00:03:50,740 --> 00:03:52,730
Check this out! Don't miss out!

116
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:54,720
You won't regret it!

117
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:56,240
You won't get ripped off!

118
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,310
Why are you cleaning it here?

119
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:05,310
You can't clean it here.

120
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:05,900
Leave.

121
00:04:05,930 --> 00:04:06,590
Okay.

122
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:09,520
I'm in the way, aren't I?

123
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,150
Why are you still sitting there? Move!

124
00:04:13,150 --> 00:04:13,670
Move it!

125
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:14,660
I am, I am.

126
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:15,830
I am moving.

127
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:19,190
Do you need your range hood cleaned?

128
00:04:19,190 --> 00:04:20,240
No, I don't.

129
00:04:20,890 --> 00:04:21,570
Go clean it outside.

130
00:04:21,570 --> 00:04:22,370
Okay.

131
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:24,230
You're blocking the entrance.

132
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:32,750
Thank you.

133
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,450
How much is this one?

134
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:36,180
This one?

135
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,810
It's our first day of business today—

136
00:04:37,810 --> 00:04:39,220
what about 45?

137
00:04:39,330 --> 00:04:40,270
Okay, 45.

138
00:04:40,330 --> 00:04:40,690
Okay.

139
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:42,770
Does it fit well?

140
00:04:42,830 --> 00:04:43,830
It fits perfectly.

141
00:04:43,830 --> 00:04:45,360
Let me tighten this for you.

142
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:45,920
Okay.

143
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:47,050
Take the money.

144
00:04:47,250 --> 00:04:47,800
Here.

145
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:48,830
Thank you.

146
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:49,930
Please pack this one up for us.

147
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:50,300
Okay.

148
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:51,630
-Okay. Thank you.
-Just a second.

149
00:04:51,630 --> 00:04:52,190
I'll put it here.

150
00:04:52,190 --> 00:04:53,050
Very nice.

151
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:53,970
Okay.

152
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,470
It really suits you.

153
00:04:55,740 --> 00:04:56,340
Thank you.

154
00:04:58,060 --> 00:04:58,430
Here.

155
00:04:58,870 --> 00:04:59,200
Here.

156
00:05:02,450 --> 00:05:02,940
Here.

157
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,040
Thank you.

158
00:05:04,050 --> 00:05:05,060
Here, I'll take it.

159
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:05,510
Would you like

160
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:06,630
a denim shirt for yourself?

161
00:05:06,630 --> 00:05:07,010
Yeah.

162
00:05:07,010 --> 00:05:08,270
Not enough money left.

163
00:05:08,430 --> 00:05:08,860
Okay.

164
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:09,930
Next time then.

165
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:10,360
Next time.

166
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:10,950
-Okay.
-Next time.

167
00:05:10,950 --> 00:05:12,590
Tell your friends about us.

168
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,140
Will do.

169
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:21,560
Twenty, thirty, forty—

170
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:22,690
I'll be right back.

171
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,160
Five.

172
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:33,540
My hero.

173
00:05:34,130 --> 00:05:34,930
Thanks, boss.

174
00:05:37,659 --> 00:05:38,720
So, starting today,

175
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,040
our little stall

176
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:41,950
is officially up and running.

177
00:05:43,630 --> 00:05:46,230
Partner, looking forward
to working with you.

178
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:47,620
Me too.

179
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:54,780
But let's get this straight first.

180
00:05:54,890 --> 00:05:56,450
I have classes from Monday to Friday.

181
00:05:56,450 --> 00:05:57,580
I can only come on weekends.

182
00:05:57,580 --> 00:05:59,940
If I hear from the film studio,
I have to go too.

183
00:05:59,940 --> 00:06:01,450
But I'll ask for leave in advance.

184
00:06:01,450 --> 00:06:02,110
No problem.

185
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:03,930
Mr. Zheng said

186
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:05,250
I need to take care of my voice.

187
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:06,950
I'll handle styling and sales,

188
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:08,160
and you do the hawking.

189
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,300
Sure thing.

190
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,310
But while I do that,

191
00:06:10,310 --> 00:06:11,190
I might also jot down notes

192
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:12,450
about life from time to time.

193
00:06:12,450 --> 00:06:13,440
No problem.

194
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:15,140
Just say you're bookkeeping.

195
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:17,510
We'll closely work together
to negotiate a good price.

196
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:18,910
How do we split the money?

197
00:06:20,270 --> 00:06:21,530
Five hundred in total;

198
00:06:21,570 --> 00:06:22,970
400 from me, 100 from you.

199
00:06:23,090 --> 00:06:24,290
Let's split it 20-80.

200
00:06:24,310 --> 00:06:25,570
Who gets 20 and who gets 80?

201
00:06:25,570 --> 00:06:27,070
I get 80 and you get 20, obviously.

202
00:06:27,070 --> 00:06:27,870
That won't do.

203
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:28,660
No?

204
00:06:28,860 --> 00:06:30,070
I should get less.

205
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,870
I borrowed my 100 from you.

206
00:06:33,770 --> 00:06:35,620
If I wanted more, I'd be doing it alone.

207
00:06:35,620 --> 00:06:37,280
I won't take advantage of you.

208
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:38,360
That 100 yuan,

209
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,760
you can pay me back later.

210
00:06:39,860 --> 00:06:40,630
Let's keep things separate.

211
00:06:40,630 --> 00:06:41,890
Business is business.

212
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:44,360
As befits someone from Wenzhou—

213
00:06:44,950 --> 00:06:45,680
very shrewd.

214
00:07:31,770 --> 00:07:32,260
Song?

215
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:33,570
Song?

216
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:35,310
Song, Little Song?

217
00:07:35,810 --> 00:07:36,540
Little Song?

218
00:07:37,159 --> 00:07:37,890
Little Song?

219
00:07:38,190 --> 00:07:38,920
Little Song,

220
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:39,980
my child.

221
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:42,040
-Keep it down, we're sleeping.
-Keep it down.

222
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,390
What are you doing this early?

223
00:07:43,390 --> 00:07:43,950
Zongbao,

224
00:07:44,180 --> 00:07:45,040
Little Song...

225
00:07:45,430 --> 00:07:46,740
My son, Little Song, is missing.

226
00:07:46,740 --> 00:07:47,670
I can't find him.

227
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:49,230
Good riddance. He stank.

228
00:07:49,420 --> 00:07:50,360
What are you saying?

229
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:51,560
Did you get rid of him?

230
00:07:51,950 --> 00:07:53,060
I don't have time for that.

231
00:07:53,060 --> 00:07:54,120
Keep looking.

232
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:54,750
Little Song?

233
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:55,450
I did.

234
00:07:55,450 --> 00:07:56,300
I've looked

235
00:07:56,540 --> 00:07:58,400
literally everywhere, Zongbao.

236
00:07:58,500 --> 00:07:59,700
-Little Song?
-Song?

237
00:07:59,890 --> 00:08:01,090
-Song?
-Little Song?

238
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:01,820
Song?

239
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,450
Was he here last night?

240
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,180
Yes.

241
00:08:04,220 --> 00:08:05,070
This... this is the dinner

242
00:08:05,070 --> 00:08:06,730
I prepared for him last night.

243
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:11,180
Might have gone out at midnight.

244
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:12,890
Go check the hallway.

245
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:14,560
Anyone got up last night?

246
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,180
I didn't.

247
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,680
Me neither.

248
00:08:20,270 --> 00:08:21,730
What about you, Xu Shengli?

249
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:23,020
I went to the bathroom.

250
00:08:23,450 --> 00:08:24,450
It was him then.

251
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:28,480
You came back after midnight, no?

252
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:30,800
Okay, case solved.

253
00:08:31,370 --> 00:08:32,429
The squirrel

254
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,549
got out of the cage

255
00:08:33,549 --> 00:08:34,750
by itself last night.

256
00:08:35,380 --> 00:08:37,000
Then the door

257
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:38,090
opened and closed,

258
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,460
and it went out to play.

259
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:41,059
Let's go look in the hallway.

260
00:08:41,409 --> 00:08:42,669
Was it you, Xu Shengli?

261
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:43,840
I'm talking to you!

262
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:44,390
Was it you?

263
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:45,000
What are you doing?

264
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,720
-I'm sleeping. Can you guys talk later?
-Zongbao.

265
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:47,550
Zongbao, you probably don't know,

266
00:08:47,550 --> 00:08:48,720
one day when neither of you were around,

267
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:49,260
he...

268
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:51,200
he said Little Song has germs

269
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:52,370
and isn't sanitary.

270
00:08:52,370 --> 00:08:53,100
He's never liked

271
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:54,010
my son!

272
00:08:54,170 --> 00:08:55,500
Can you guys talk later?

273
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:56,280
Get up.

274
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:56,950
No.

275
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:57,810
I said get up!

276
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:58,550
I won't!

277
00:08:58,670 --> 00:08:59,750
Get up now!

278
00:09:04,620 --> 00:09:06,150
Zongbao, it's Little Song!

279
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:09,840
I knew it was you, Xu Shengli!

280
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:10,460
Move!

281
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:19,570
Those nightmares in 108—

282
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,230
what are they up to now?

283
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,320
Coming through. Move, move.

284
00:09:24,140 --> 00:09:25,410
Sounds like a homicide.

285
00:09:25,410 --> 00:09:26,340
Call the police.

286
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,800
Don't talk nonsense.

287
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:30,450
Open the door!

288
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:32,770
It's me, Little Northeasterner.
Open the door!

289
00:09:32,770 --> 00:09:34,050
If someone really gets killed,

290
00:09:34,050 --> 00:09:36,050
we're not going to stay here anymore.

291
00:09:36,050 --> 00:09:37,250
I'm going to get the key.

292
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:38,450
Officer Tang is here!

293
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,170
Little Northeasterner!

294
00:09:40,220 --> 00:09:40,820
Mayday!

295
00:09:40,870 --> 00:09:42,100
Officer Tang is here!

296
00:09:45,510 --> 00:09:46,620
You guys are going to

297
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:47,860
ruin my business!

298
00:09:48,340 --> 00:09:48,820
Can't you manage

299
00:09:48,820 --> 00:09:50,480
your little hostel properly?

300
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,550
It's causing trouble every day!

301
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:53,360
I come here eight times a week,

302
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:53,890
you know?

303
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:57,390
Right, right.

304
00:10:00,170 --> 00:10:03,260
[The memory lives on, the legacy endures,
forever with us]

305
00:10:00,410 --> 00:10:01,680
Xu Shengli.

306
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:04,530
Have you been here a week yet?

307
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,200
The police have come twice already.

308
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:09,510
I really regret

309
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:10,200
bringing you here

310
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,760
from the train station.

311
00:10:12,770 --> 00:10:14,290
Whatever is going on in 108—

312
00:10:14,290 --> 00:10:15,370
just let me know today

313
00:10:15,370 --> 00:10:16,820
if you can sort it out.

314
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,320
If this place is too small

315
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,220
for a big shot like you,

316
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:20,750
I won't try to keep you.

317
00:10:21,050 --> 00:10:22,580
For six yuan a day for the bed

318
00:10:22,630 --> 00:10:24,010
I get 600 yuan's worth of hassle.

319
00:10:24,010 --> 00:10:25,440
Can anyone stand this?

320
00:10:27,750 --> 00:10:29,010
Sorry for the trouble.

321
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,480
I'm really sorry.

322
00:10:32,460 --> 00:10:33,990
I'll figure something out.

323
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:35,860
My condolences.

324
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:37,570
And another thing.

325
00:10:38,790 --> 00:10:41,480
It's not easy for anyone out here.

326
00:10:42,010 --> 00:10:43,810
Don't back people into a corner.

327
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,370
Even a worm will turn!

328
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:01,440
Zongbao,

329
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:04,570
Liangliang,

330
00:11:06,630 --> 00:11:08,290
Little Song was just like you.

331
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:11,360
You're all my closest family.

332
00:11:11,670 --> 00:11:12,820
He came to Beijing with me

333
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:14,150
all the way from Shanxi.

334
00:11:14,650 --> 00:11:16,980
We traveled thousands of miles together.

335
00:11:17,630 --> 00:11:18,120
Okay.

336
00:11:18,460 --> 00:11:19,940
In so many lonely moments,

337
00:11:21,360 --> 00:11:22,490
he was there with me.

338
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:25,450
[The memory lives on, the legacy endures,
forever with us]

339
00:11:23,270 --> 00:11:24,390
On so many cold nights,

340
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:25,390
he warmed my heart

341
00:11:25,510 --> 00:11:26,670
with his warmth.

342
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:28,900
In the scorching summer,

343
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,300
its playfulness

344
00:11:30,330 --> 00:11:31,750
brought me true relief.

345
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:33,540
Song...

346
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,410
we were friends.

347
00:11:37,890 --> 00:11:39,130
We were father and son.

348
00:11:39,130 --> 00:11:41,900
[The memory lives on, the legacy endures,
forever with us]

349
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:40,530
We were fellow sufferers

350
00:11:40,530 --> 00:11:41,240
and family.

351
00:11:41,980 --> 00:11:43,640
But since you've been with me,

352
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,480
we've only shared hardships—

353
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,290
we never got to share any good time.

354
00:11:47,290 --> 00:11:48,200
I haven't been able

355
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,580
to give you a single day of happiness,

356
00:11:49,580 --> 00:11:51,200
and now... now you've been killed

357
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,530
by a bad guy.

358
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:54,360
-Okay. Okay.
-Here's my word—

359
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:55,920
if I don't avenge you,

360
00:11:56,050 --> 00:11:57,160
I'm not a man.

361
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,720
Okay, okay...

362
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:00,630
My condolences.

363
00:12:00,670 --> 00:12:01,510
My condolences.

364
00:12:01,510 --> 00:12:02,520
My condolences.

365
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:03,370
Cao Ye,

366
00:12:04,910 --> 00:12:06,240
I really didn't mean to.

367
00:12:07,030 --> 00:12:08,080
I really don't know

368
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,340
when it got onto my bed.

369
00:12:09,580 --> 00:12:09,980
But...

370
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,000
I did crush it.

371
00:12:13,340 --> 00:12:14,120
I apologize.

372
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:15,900
Okay now.

373
00:12:18,390 --> 00:12:19,250
I'm someone who

374
00:12:19,650 --> 00:12:20,980
doesn't usually drink.

375
00:12:22,860 --> 00:12:25,000
Take this as my apology.

376
00:12:31,580 --> 00:12:32,960
What do you mean "take this as"?

377
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:34,720
Even at a grave, you pour three cups.

378
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:35,270
One cup?

379
00:12:35,340 --> 00:12:36,740
Who are you trying to impress?

380
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:38,010
Is this how you Shandong people do things?

381
00:12:38,010 --> 00:12:39,030
Don't... Stop, stop.

382
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:40,410
Why are you covering my mouth?

383
00:12:40,410 --> 00:12:41,140
Tell me then.

384
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,600
What do I have to do

385
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:44,390
to put this behind us?

386
00:12:44,390 --> 00:12:45,980
Listen, Xu Shengli.

387
00:12:46,170 --> 00:12:46,970
In this world,

388
00:12:47,010 --> 00:12:48,340
it's not like for everything that happens,

389
00:12:48,340 --> 00:12:49,240
you just say "sorry,"

390
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:49,910
and I have to forgive you.

391
00:12:49,910 --> 00:12:50,460
Alright now.

392
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:51,730
I don't accept your apology.

393
00:12:51,730 --> 00:12:52,730
I don't accept it!

394
00:12:52,790 --> 00:12:54,420
A life for a life.

395
00:12:54,460 --> 00:12:55,360
That was a life.

396
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:55,980
A life!

397
00:12:55,980 --> 00:12:57,240
Okay, okay, okay.

398
00:12:58,700 --> 00:12:59,360
A life, yeah?

399
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,290
My condolences.

400
00:13:03,610 --> 00:13:04,270
Why are you drinking—

401
00:13:04,270 --> 00:13:05,340
Let him drink.

402
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:08,170
But... the liquor...

403
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:09,240
He's finishing it!

404
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,200
Leave it.

405
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:12,010
Alright, alright, alright.

406
00:13:12,010 --> 00:13:13,580
Stop drinking. Stop drinking!

407
00:13:13,580 --> 00:13:14,710
Hey, stop drinking.

408
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:16,150
You'll harm yourself...

409
00:13:16,820 --> 00:13:18,220
If this is not enough,
I'll go buy some more.

410
00:13:18,220 --> 00:13:18,960
No, no, don't.

411
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:19,580
I'm laying my life down

412
00:13:19,580 --> 00:13:20,580
right here today.

413
00:13:20,630 --> 00:13:22,250
Enough with your drunken fit!

414
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:22,870
You were asking

415
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:23,740
how to put this behind us?

416
00:13:23,740 --> 00:13:25,100
Fine. I'll tell you, Xu Shengli.

417
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,160
Bring Little Song

418
00:13:26,270 --> 00:13:27,670
back to me safe and sound,

419
00:13:27,670 --> 00:13:28,820
and I'll put this behind us.

420
00:13:28,820 --> 00:13:29,810
Can you do that?

421
00:13:29,870 --> 00:13:31,510
You can't!

422
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:33,580
I know,

423
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:37,660
you guys have a problem with me.

424
00:13:39,010 --> 00:13:40,850
You think I'm arrogant.

425
00:13:41,650 --> 00:13:42,340
I admit it.

426
00:13:43,980 --> 00:13:45,240
When I first came here,

427
00:13:45,670 --> 00:13:46,840
I was arrogant.

428
00:13:47,770 --> 00:13:48,700
But I have never

429
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:50,550
looked down on anyone.

430
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,500
We met by chance.

431
00:13:54,290 --> 00:13:56,290
Getting to live under the same roof

432
00:13:56,340 --> 00:13:57,840
is serendipity.

433
00:13:58,650 --> 00:14:00,590
Why can't we just

434
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:03,540
live in peace...

435
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,030
in peace...

436
00:14:09,010 --> 00:14:09,780
Shengli?

437
00:14:10,510 --> 00:14:11,080
Shengli?

438
00:14:12,050 --> 00:14:13,980
You're going to get yourself sick.

439
00:14:14,340 --> 00:14:16,210
You two are really something, aren't you?

440
00:14:16,210 --> 00:14:16,940
A Beijinger

441
00:14:17,010 --> 00:14:18,100
and a Shanxi guy

442
00:14:18,130 --> 00:14:19,770
got a Shandong guy this wasted.

443
00:14:19,770 --> 00:14:22,740
-Going to brag for the rest of your lives?
-He drank it himself.

444
00:14:22,740 --> 00:14:23,710
Xu Shengli.

445
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:25,400
A call for you.

446
00:14:27,250 --> 00:14:28,180
What's going on?

447
00:14:30,510 --> 00:14:31,370
He drank

448
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:32,740
half a bottle himself.

449
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:34,820
Xu Shengli.

450
00:14:35,340 --> 00:14:36,080
A call for you.

451
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:36,320
Shengli.

452
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,450
It's Director Weng.

453
00:14:45,030 --> 00:14:45,490
What...

454
00:14:47,290 --> 00:14:48,530
What's going on now,

455
00:14:48,550 --> 00:14:49,460
my lords?

456
00:14:57,980 --> 00:14:58,580
Zhuang...

457
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:00,580
Why are you here?

458
00:15:10,670 --> 00:15:12,670
Director Weng called me yesterday?

459
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:16,340
No, no.

460
00:15:16,410 --> 00:15:16,870
What are you doing?

461
00:15:16,870 --> 00:15:18,130
I have to call him back.

462
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:19,510
What are you doing? Sit down!

463
00:15:19,510 --> 00:15:21,370
Sit down. Are you out of your mind?

464
00:15:21,410 --> 00:15:22,870
You got yourself acute alcohol poisoning,

465
00:15:22,870 --> 00:15:23,670
are you aware?

466
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,080
You had a fever over 40 degrees.

467
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:26,810
Even your trachea got swollen.

468
00:15:34,130 --> 00:15:36,820
I still have to call him back...

469
00:15:37,390 --> 00:15:38,620
When you're back later today,

470
00:15:38,620 --> 00:15:40,750
can you call Director Weng back for me?

471
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,320
Lie down first.

472
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:50,570
Don't worry.

473
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:53,250
I'll explain it to him when I'm back.

474
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:55,410
But please don't tell him

475
00:15:55,410 --> 00:15:56,840
that I'm hospitalized because of drinking.

476
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:58,100
Now you're scared?

477
00:15:59,250 --> 00:16:00,650
Why did you drink so much?

478
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:04,910
Did the guys in 108

479
00:16:04,910 --> 00:16:05,670
force you to drink?

480
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:06,170
No.

481
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,860
It has nothing to do with them.

482
00:16:10,630 --> 00:16:12,430
Drinking so much when you can't.

483
00:16:13,010 --> 00:16:13,770
Reckless.

484
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:21,690
I think we've taken this

485
00:16:22,770 --> 00:16:24,350
a bit too far.

486
00:16:24,620 --> 00:16:25,440
How so?

487
00:16:27,940 --> 00:16:29,120
Are you betraying us?

488
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:29,860
No, no.

489
00:16:30,150 --> 00:16:32,140
It's just, after all this trouble,

490
00:16:32,390 --> 00:16:33,920
I'm feeling kind of guilty.

491
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:35,630
Zongbao.

492
00:16:36,940 --> 00:16:37,550
Well,

493
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:39,480
one thing led to another,

494
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,610
and we ended up here.

495
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:43,890
He's in the hospital now,

496
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:44,490
isn't he?

497
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,130
Saying this now...

498
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:47,960
is too late.

499
00:16:48,630 --> 00:16:50,300
Maybe in the future,

500
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:51,470
if there's any

501
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,670
Tom, Dick, or Harry

502
00:16:52,740 --> 00:16:53,370
who joins us,

503
00:16:53,370 --> 00:16:54,500
we can give him some—

504
00:16:58,220 --> 00:16:59,220
You didn't knock.

505
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:00,360
Is that polite?

506
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:01,620
With unreasonable people,

507
00:17:01,620 --> 00:17:03,200
there's no need for politeness.

508
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,730
Who's being unreasonable?

509
00:17:04,849 --> 00:17:05,960
Is it fun for you guys

510
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:07,640
to bully people all the time?

511
00:17:07,980 --> 00:17:09,069
Do you have to drive people out

512
00:17:09,069 --> 00:17:10,109
for your own enjoyment?

513
00:17:10,109 --> 00:17:11,140
We're all from out of town.

514
00:17:11,140 --> 00:17:12,200
Is this necessary?

515
00:17:15,829 --> 00:17:17,140
He's very sick right now.

516
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:17,640
You're all

517
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,069
responsible for that.

518
00:17:19,220 --> 00:17:21,079
You should pay the medical bills.

519
00:17:21,310 --> 00:17:22,829
Discussing money is a bit too much.

520
00:17:22,829 --> 00:17:23,980
Well... my son, Little Song,

521
00:17:23,980 --> 00:17:25,460
was crushed to death by him.

522
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:27,109
I didn't ask him for money.

523
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:28,069
Who's responsible?

524
00:17:28,069 --> 00:17:29,030
Who's paying?

525
00:17:29,110 --> 00:17:30,640
He drank the liquor himself.

526
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:31,770
Why should we pay

527
00:17:31,770 --> 00:17:32,590
half the medical bills?

528
00:17:32,590 --> 00:17:32,810
Right.

529
00:17:32,810 --> 00:17:33,550
Besides,

530
00:17:33,850 --> 00:17:34,750
he grinds his teeth, farts,

531
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:35,700
smacks his lips,

532
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:36,700
and talks in sleep.

533
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:38,030
Who could stand all that?

534
00:17:38,030 --> 00:17:38,530
Exactly.

535
00:17:38,530 --> 00:17:39,310
If you can stand it,

536
00:17:39,310 --> 00:17:40,330
let him stay in your room.

537
00:17:40,330 --> 00:17:41,000
Tell me about it.

538
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:41,740
So he...

539
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:43,310
he just didn't sleep well for one night.

540
00:17:43,310 --> 00:17:44,290
He drank a bit and got like that.

541
00:17:44,290 --> 00:17:45,510
But what about us on a daily basis? Right?

542
00:17:45,510 --> 00:17:46,090
Exactly.

543
00:17:46,550 --> 00:17:48,350
Are you going to sort this or not?

544
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:54,700
Are you going to sort this?

545
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:55,420
Don't think just because

546
00:17:55,420 --> 00:17:56,070
you're a girl,

547
00:17:56,070 --> 00:17:57,110
you can yell at us

548
00:17:57,180 --> 00:17:57,770
and we have to

549
00:17:57,770 --> 00:17:58,420
indulge you

550
00:17:58,420 --> 00:17:58,900
and put up

551
00:17:58,900 --> 00:17:59,560
with you.

552
00:17:59,610 --> 00:18:00,520
A girl gets to

553
00:18:00,660 --> 00:18:01,270
blow up

554
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:02,070
and kill?

555
00:18:02,270 --> 00:18:04,270
I'm curious to see, here in Beijing—

556
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:10,290
What...

557
00:18:10,740 --> 00:18:11,830
What are you doing?

558
00:18:11,830 --> 00:18:12,330
Zhuang Zhuang!

559
00:18:12,330 --> 00:18:12,960
I... I...

560
00:18:13,030 --> 00:18:13,920
You planning to move out of here

561
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:14,480
or what?

562
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,050
Such a waste!

563
00:18:16,750 --> 00:18:17,610
Zhuang Zhuang.

564
00:18:18,290 --> 00:18:19,470
Stop walking.

565
00:18:19,530 --> 00:18:21,270
Messing with a young master of Beijing—

566
00:18:21,270 --> 00:18:22,610
you'll have nowhere to go in this city.

567
00:18:22,610 --> 00:18:23,610
I don't care if you have anywhere to go.

568
00:18:23,610 --> 00:18:24,570
You have to pay for that jar
of chili sauce.

569
00:18:24,570 --> 00:18:25,140
You...

570
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:34,020
What now?

571
00:18:34,070 --> 00:18:34,800
What do we do?

572
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:36,810
Let's go back and discuss.

573
00:18:36,810 --> 00:18:39,070
What are you doing? Why are you shouting?

574
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:40,520
Why are you at our door?

575
00:18:44,010 --> 00:18:45,540
Isn't this Miss Celebrity?

576
00:18:45,550 --> 00:18:47,350
I was just about to report to you.

577
00:18:47,510 --> 00:18:48,870
Our wish

578
00:18:49,030 --> 00:18:50,230
is about to come true.

579
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:52,310
What are you talking about?

580
00:18:52,310 --> 00:18:53,810
That annoying guy in our room

581
00:18:53,810 --> 00:18:55,670
is moving out soon.

582
00:18:56,380 --> 00:18:58,840
This one in your room
won't stay long either.

583
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:00,870
She can't leave.

584
00:19:01,090 --> 00:19:02,130
She is my sister.

585
00:19:02,380 --> 00:19:03,950
If you two dare to bully my sister,

586
00:19:03,950 --> 00:19:04,740
you're dead.

587
00:19:04,850 --> 00:19:05,650
Wait, your...

588
00:19:05,850 --> 00:19:07,380
-Her sister?
-Your sister?

589
00:19:12,460 --> 00:19:14,290
How did she become her sister?

590
00:19:21,090 --> 00:19:22,330
You've fully recovered?

591
00:19:22,330 --> 00:19:24,250
My vitality is surging back.

592
00:19:24,290 --> 00:19:25,890
A registered parcel for you.

593
00:19:26,770 --> 00:19:27,700
Let it surge back slowly.

594
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:28,250
Or just don't hold me

595
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:29,780
responsible for anything.

596
00:19:34,790 --> 00:19:35,390
Sign here.

597
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,960
I know nothing about scriptwriting,

598
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:41,900
but looks like you're getting

599
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:42,850
better and better at it.

600
00:19:42,850 --> 00:19:43,580
I mean, look,

601
00:19:43,610 --> 00:19:45,090
these letters with Capital Film Studio

602
00:19:45,090 --> 00:19:46,490
are going back and forth.

603
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:52,350
Two cents for radishes.

604
00:19:52,350 --> 00:19:53,550
Get me a bunch a those.

605
00:19:56,850 --> 00:19:58,450
Why are you here again?

606
00:19:58,660 --> 00:19:59,740
Our backlog of scripts

607
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:00,570
have all been sent back.

608
00:20:00,570 --> 00:20:01,970
Didn't you receive them?

609
00:20:02,090 --> 00:20:02,570
Mr. Wu,

610
00:20:03,420 --> 00:20:05,420
I'm not looking for Director Weng today.

611
00:20:05,420 --> 00:20:06,550
I'm looking for you.

612
00:20:06,810 --> 00:20:08,470
But why are you looking for me?

613
00:20:09,420 --> 00:20:10,680
I received the script.

614
00:20:12,570 --> 00:20:13,900
I just wanted to ask you,

615
00:20:14,010 --> 00:20:15,410
did you read this script?

616
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:17,810
Isn't it obvious?

617
00:20:17,810 --> 00:20:19,740
Just tell me, did you read it or not?

618
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:22,100
Look, I...

619
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:24,160
Well... what do you want?

620
00:20:28,570 --> 00:20:29,630
Within the script,

621
00:20:30,180 --> 00:20:31,380
I glued three places.

622
00:20:32,510 --> 00:20:33,570
I don't assume you read it

623
00:20:33,570 --> 00:20:35,300
and glued them back, or did you?

624
00:20:37,070 --> 00:20:37,810
Mr. Wu,

625
00:20:38,570 --> 00:20:39,340
everyone,

626
00:20:40,010 --> 00:20:41,870
I really regard you as my seniors.

627
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:43,380
I just hoped

628
00:20:43,420 --> 00:20:44,660
that you could give me some guidance

629
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:45,460
and advice.

630
00:20:45,530 --> 00:20:46,460
That's all.

631
00:20:47,850 --> 00:20:48,570
I am just

632
00:20:48,610 --> 00:20:50,090
a young man with a dream.

633
00:20:50,940 --> 00:20:52,020
I so longed to meet

634
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:53,320
mentors like you,

635
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:55,110
seniors who could guide me.

636
00:20:55,350 --> 00:20:56,740
Like seeing a lighthouse in the dark,

637
00:20:56,740 --> 00:20:57,800
showing me the way.

638
00:20:57,900 --> 00:20:58,900
Are you not willing to shed

639
00:20:58,900 --> 00:20:59,980
even that little bit of light?

640
00:20:59,980 --> 00:21:01,690
What dream? What lighthouse?

641
00:21:01,810 --> 00:21:03,110
This is a studio.

642
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:05,700
We have a heavy workload.

643
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:08,200
Young man,

644
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,530
I'll tell you the truth.

645
00:21:09,550 --> 00:21:10,830
Director Weng never asked us

646
00:21:10,830 --> 00:21:12,160
to read your script.

647
00:21:12,770 --> 00:21:13,830
Do you understand?

648
00:21:18,590 --> 00:21:19,640
If you want to wait,

649
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:20,550
go ahead and wait.

650
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:21,280
I don't mind.

651
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,640
But don't wait in the office.

652
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:23,550
We're all just trying

653
00:21:23,550 --> 00:21:24,480
to make a living.

654
00:21:24,590 --> 00:21:26,590
No one is here to play house with you.

655
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:33,950
Young man,

656
00:21:34,270 --> 00:21:35,480
take the script back

657
00:21:35,510 --> 00:21:36,590
and polish it some more,

658
00:21:36,590 --> 00:21:37,830
and send it to us again.

659
00:21:37,830 --> 00:21:38,380
Trust me,

660
00:21:38,510 --> 00:21:40,040
we will definitely read it.

661
00:21:56,590 --> 00:21:57,450
Unbelievable.

662
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:26,140
Reading it again?

663
00:22:26,790 --> 00:22:28,130
How many times have you

664
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:29,820
read it now?

665
00:22:30,350 --> 00:22:31,370
You must know it by heart now.

666
00:22:31,370 --> 00:22:32,660
Fancy playing a role?

667
00:22:34,070 --> 00:22:35,000
I haven't finished it yet.

668
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:35,730
I have to say,

669
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:39,310
my son wrote a pretty interesting script.

670
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:40,640
As I read it,

671
00:22:40,680 --> 00:22:41,850
I really got into it.

672
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:44,110
I think you are interesting.

673
00:22:45,830 --> 00:22:46,560
-Why?
-Well,

674
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,790
when he was home,

675
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:50,270
you were always against him.

676
00:22:50,270 --> 00:22:50,920
Now he's gone,

677
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:52,180
you tore up his script,

678
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:54,660
and now you taped it
back together to read it.

679
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,650
I mean, that's

680
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:56,480
all in the past now,

681
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:57,810
can't you just let it go?

682
00:22:58,070 --> 00:22:59,320
I tore it up, yes,

683
00:22:59,350 --> 00:23:00,550
but now I've taped it back together,

684
00:23:00,550 --> 00:23:01,000
okay?

685
00:23:02,070 --> 00:23:03,640
Am I not allowed to make mistakes?

686
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:04,350
Fine, fine.

687
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:05,270
Okay.

688
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:07,780
What are you doing?

689
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:08,880
I'm selling these books.

690
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:10,690
You... you can't sell these.

691
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:11,850
These are all his things.

692
00:23:11,850 --> 00:23:12,480
If he comes back and can't find them,

693
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:13,590
he'll be upset.

694
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:14,720
Is he coming back?

695
00:23:14,830 --> 00:23:16,290
Why wouldn't he come back?

696
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:17,900
Where else would he go?

697
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:19,680
Didn't you drive him away?

698
00:23:19,790 --> 00:23:20,510
So what?

699
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:22,420
You're going to drive me away too,

700
00:23:22,420 --> 00:23:23,060
and be...

701
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:24,720
and be the only one left in this house?

702
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:26,030
I'm not trying to drive you away.

703
00:23:26,030 --> 00:23:26,960
I'm just saying,

704
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:28,580
all these books in here,

705
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:30,880
you bought him every single one of them.

706
00:23:31,270 --> 00:23:32,960
Throughout middle school and high school,

707
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,330
you bought him whatever he wanted.

708
00:23:34,330 --> 00:23:35,350
Now he's grown up

709
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,400
and wants to write scripts,

710
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:37,150
you tell him,

711
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:39,300
writing doesn't pay the bills.

712
00:23:39,350 --> 00:23:40,880
You even tore up his script.

713
00:23:41,150 --> 00:23:42,000
Now he's gone to Beijing,

714
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,400
and you're suddenly reading the script.

715
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:46,000
Aren't you saying one thing
but doing another?

716
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:47,000
I tore it up, yes.

717
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,550
But I've taped it back together, no?

718
00:23:48,550 --> 00:23:49,800
I've fixed it. Okay?

719
00:23:50,070 --> 00:23:50,510
Okay, okay.

720
00:23:50,510 --> 00:23:52,430
You just won't let this go.

721
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:52,970
Fine.

722
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:53,310
Alright, alright.

723
00:23:53,310 --> 00:23:55,220
Stop... stop this.

724
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:57,370
Let's just eat, okay?

725
00:23:57,510 --> 00:23:59,110
I've got it all ready for you.

726
00:24:00,310 --> 00:24:01,610
Going to Beijing...

727
00:24:01,750 --> 00:24:03,610
It's not that I don't support him.

728
00:24:04,790 --> 00:24:06,650
But what kind of place is Beijing?

729
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:08,380
It's full of talented people.

730
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:10,250
I'm just worried about him.

731
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:14,880
I'm worried he'll face rejection there.

732
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:15,540
So,

733
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:18,330
I'd rather he curse me in his heart,

734
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,690
than have him suffer.

735
00:24:24,070 --> 00:24:25,000
No parent

736
00:24:25,030 --> 00:24:27,090
would not want their child to do well.

737
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:30,410
Alright.

738
00:24:33,060 --> 00:24:34,260
I'll go get your food.

739
00:25:03,550 --> 00:25:05,150
Can I help you with anything?

740
00:25:05,830 --> 00:25:06,310
No need.

741
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:07,750
Don't be mad.

742
00:25:07,790 --> 00:25:09,030
What are you mad about?

743
00:25:09,030 --> 00:25:09,770
Honestly.

744
00:25:18,010 --> 00:25:19,740
You keep the light on all night.

745
00:25:19,850 --> 00:25:20,610
Trying to keep us all up

746
00:25:20,610 --> 00:25:21,700
until we drop?

747
00:25:22,660 --> 00:25:24,180
It's just a light.

748
00:25:24,180 --> 00:25:25,090
I'll adjust it for you,

749
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:25,660
okay?

750
00:25:25,660 --> 00:25:26,610
What good

751
00:25:26,660 --> 00:25:27,720
is all the whining?

752
00:25:28,980 --> 00:25:30,180
Seriously? Isn't that selfish?

753
00:25:30,180 --> 00:25:30,810
That's how you do it?

754
00:25:30,810 --> 00:25:31,220
How is Zongbao

755
00:25:31,220 --> 00:25:32,330
supposed to sleep?

756
00:25:32,980 --> 00:25:34,710
You should adjust it like this.

757
00:25:36,220 --> 00:25:36,790
You like the light so much?

758
00:25:36,790 --> 00:25:37,740
Can't live without it, yeah?

759
00:25:37,740 --> 00:25:38,660
Then shine it on yourself.

760
00:25:38,660 --> 00:25:40,120
Right on your face. There.

761
00:25:42,220 --> 00:25:43,530
Hey, what are you doing?

762
00:25:43,530 --> 00:25:45,350
The light's gone, noise is on?

763
00:25:45,530 --> 00:25:46,510
Shut your mouth.

764
00:25:46,570 --> 00:25:48,090
-Are you done?
-Is the noise my fault?

765
00:25:48,090 --> 00:25:49,050
Listen!

766
00:25:52,290 --> 00:25:52,960
I quit my secure job

767
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:54,110
at the state factory

768
00:25:54,180 --> 00:25:55,760
to come to Beijing.

769
00:25:56,740 --> 00:25:57,540
Director Weng

770
00:25:58,270 --> 00:25:59,570
is my lifeline.

771
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:01,470
I missed his call.

772
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:02,650
That is my fate.

773
00:26:03,140 --> 00:26:04,740
If I can't see Director Weng,

774
00:26:04,740 --> 00:26:05,450
I won't know

775
00:26:05,470 --> 00:26:06,330
what to do next.

776
00:26:06,740 --> 00:26:08,180
But I have to stay in Beijing.

777
00:26:08,180 --> 00:26:09,580
I have to support myself.

778
00:26:09,740 --> 00:26:11,420
So I sell clothes during the day,

779
00:26:11,420 --> 00:26:13,000
and I write at night.

780
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:15,240
Whether you can put up with me

781
00:26:15,570 --> 00:26:16,570
is your business.

782
00:26:17,460 --> 00:26:18,770
And I don't know how you guys

783
00:26:18,770 --> 00:26:19,810
make a living.

784
00:26:19,980 --> 00:26:20,980
But let me ask you—

785
00:26:21,330 --> 00:26:21,940
if someone

786
00:26:21,940 --> 00:26:23,670
tries to ruin your livelihood—

787
00:26:24,570 --> 00:26:26,300
tries to ruin your livelihood,

788
00:26:28,980 --> 00:26:30,840
would you fight them to the death?

789
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,810
Honestly, you two.

790
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:55,200
Everyone has a place in their heart

791
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:56,040
that is

792
00:26:56,070 --> 00:26:57,720
more important than their life.

793
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:59,440
You can't touch that.

794
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:01,880
You two know that better than anyone.

795
00:27:03,140 --> 00:27:03,920
All of us

796
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:05,160
left home

797
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:06,350
on our own.

798
00:27:08,330 --> 00:27:09,460
It hasn't been easy.

799
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:10,310
Right?

800
00:27:24,830 --> 00:27:26,570
This kid is a good kid.

801
00:27:26,660 --> 00:27:28,310
Look how angry he was just now.

802
00:27:28,310 --> 00:27:30,060
But he didn't touch your sax.

803
00:27:30,790 --> 00:27:32,520
He didn't touch your painting.

804
00:27:33,530 --> 00:27:35,400
Let's just let it go.

805
00:27:36,510 --> 00:27:37,050
Okay?

806
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:21,650
Screenwriter Xu, that speech just now

807
00:28:22,850 --> 00:28:24,640
was quite impassioned.

808
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:26,720
I'm sorry.

809
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:28,450
I got a little carried away.

810
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:30,100
You should be passionate.

811
00:28:30,110 --> 00:28:32,110
How can you create without passion?

812
00:28:37,360 --> 00:28:37,800
Right.

813
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:43,750
Why are you still up?

814
00:28:44,070 --> 00:28:45,270
I came up for a stroll.

815
00:28:56,050 --> 00:28:57,650
If it's too noisy down there,

816
00:28:57,680 --> 00:28:59,110
I think this place is nice.

817
00:28:59,110 --> 00:29:00,030
It's quiet.

818
00:29:01,290 --> 00:29:02,950
Perfect for writing scripts.

819
00:29:07,060 --> 00:29:07,580
Yes...

820
00:29:08,310 --> 00:29:08,640
Here.

821
00:29:10,090 --> 00:29:10,510
Try it.

822
00:29:13,050 --> 00:29:13,510
This...

823
00:29:17,330 --> 00:29:17,880
I...

824
00:29:20,830 --> 00:29:21,890
Does it feel right?

825
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:23,410
This... this works.

826
00:29:24,290 --> 00:29:25,130
Work hard.

827
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:26,880
Make a name for yourself.

828
00:29:27,030 --> 00:29:28,690
Show everyone what you can do.

829
00:29:32,750 --> 00:29:33,430
Very nice.

830
00:29:34,110 --> 00:29:35,770
You look like a model student.

831
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:37,950
Work hard.

832
00:29:38,110 --> 00:29:39,410
Get famous soon,

833
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:40,790
and pay me back.

834
00:29:43,510 --> 00:29:44,000
Okay.

835
00:29:44,860 --> 00:29:45,920
Goodbye, Teacher.

836
00:29:59,950 --> 00:30:03,720
[Yingkelai Beijing-Style Cuisine]

837
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:21,500
Honey,

838
00:30:22,020 --> 00:30:23,220
get some spiced beef.

839
00:30:25,990 --> 00:30:29,380
[Food Pickup]

840
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:27,560
Hello,

841
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:29,920
two bowls of porridge and
four fried dough sticks.

842
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,680
[Beijing-Style Homemade Dishes]

843
00:30:30,270 --> 00:30:31,140
Let's sit here.

844
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:35,600
[Food Pickup]

845
00:30:32,850 --> 00:30:34,700
Hello, a bowl of soy milk

846
00:30:34,830 --> 00:30:36,360
and two fried dough sticks.

847
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:46,580
[Yingkelai Beijing-Style Cuisine]

848
00:31:17,470 --> 00:31:19,400
[Yingkelai Beijing-Style Cuisine]

849
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,140
Throughout Russia,

850
00:31:19,330 --> 00:31:20,850
over half of all the "Bulajis"

851
00:31:20,850 --> 00:31:22,060
were imported by me.

852
00:31:22,590 --> 00:31:24,450
You don't know what a "Bulaji" is?

853
00:31:24,570 --> 00:31:26,330
A "Bulaji" is a dress.

854
00:31:27,900 --> 00:31:29,190
The dresses... You...

855
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:30,040
[Honest Owner That Returns Lost Items]

856
00:31:29,500 --> 00:31:30,200
Listen,

857
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:31,160
I make tens of thousands a day.

858
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:32,610
Would I default on that little bit?

859
00:31:32,610 --> 00:31:33,500
I'm still answering your call,

860
00:31:33,500 --> 00:31:34,560
I'm still here.

861
00:31:35,050 --> 00:31:36,720
Hello? I can't hear you. Hello?

862
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:37,220
Hello?

863
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:39,800
I can't hear you. Talk later.

864
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:41,600
Hounding me all day long.

865
00:31:41,960 --> 00:31:42,960
What can I get you?

866
00:31:44,660 --> 00:31:45,220
Mr. Tao,

867
00:31:45,250 --> 00:31:46,580
don't you recognize me?

868
00:31:47,270 --> 00:31:48,020
Jun?

869
00:31:48,380 --> 00:31:49,920
You changed your hairstyle.

870
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:51,250
Wasn't it slicked back?

871
00:31:51,270 --> 00:31:52,800
I'll get a perm afterwards.

872
00:31:53,140 --> 00:31:54,500
Where's your own son, Liangliang?

873
00:31:54,500 --> 00:31:55,290
That little brat.

874
00:31:55,290 --> 00:31:56,310
I don't know where he went.

875
00:31:56,310 --> 00:31:57,460
Probably went to do art.

876
00:31:57,460 --> 00:31:58,970
As long as he's alive.

877
00:31:59,330 --> 00:32:00,940
He doesn't come here as often as you do.

878
00:32:00,940 --> 00:32:02,510
I'm visiting you on his behalf.

879
00:32:02,510 --> 00:32:03,380
What can I get you?

880
00:32:03,380 --> 00:32:04,050
The usual.

881
00:32:04,160 --> 00:32:05,070
About 150 grams of beef.

882
00:32:05,070 --> 00:32:06,870
And noodles with soybean paste.

883
00:32:08,970 --> 00:32:10,970
I don't have change. Only hundreds.

884
00:32:12,090 --> 00:32:12,950
Next time then.

885
00:32:14,510 --> 00:32:15,120
Generous.

886
00:32:15,710 --> 00:32:17,310
Don't be shy to ask next time.

887
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:18,810
A bottle of soda.

888
00:32:19,250 --> 00:32:20,770
You sure can eat and drink.

889
00:32:40,250 --> 00:32:41,240
I'm off, Mr. Tao.

890
00:32:41,790 --> 00:32:42,990
Money is on the table.

891
00:32:49,940 --> 00:32:51,340
Check this out. How is it?

892
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:53,640
Why are you

893
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:54,960
wearing a raincoat on a sunny day?

894
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:56,500
I'm wearing a raincoat on the outside,

895
00:32:56,500 --> 00:32:58,000
and a short-sleeved shirt inside.

896
00:32:58,000 --> 00:32:59,270
I'm trying to display our clothes

897
00:32:59,270 --> 00:33:00,520
as much as possible.

898
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:02,210
Don't be silly. Take it off.

899
00:33:02,380 --> 00:33:03,070
Aren't you hot?

900
00:33:03,070 --> 00:33:03,900
Not at all.

901
00:33:04,070 --> 00:33:04,480
Look.

902
00:33:05,530 --> 00:33:06,380
I'm not hot.

903
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:07,960
Funny dude, huh?

904
00:33:08,250 --> 00:33:09,650
Don't mind him.

905
00:33:09,940 --> 00:33:10,830
Take a look at the clothes.

906
00:33:10,830 --> 00:33:11,420
I like this one.

907
00:33:11,420 --> 00:33:12,580
Check this out!

908
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:13,550
Don't miss out!

909
00:33:13,550 --> 00:33:14,920
Come visit again.

910
00:33:15,100 --> 00:33:15,500
Okay.

911
00:33:15,510 --> 00:33:16,320
-Sure.
-Here.

912
00:33:16,750 --> 00:33:17,240
Thank you.

913
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:17,840
Thank you.

914
00:33:23,570 --> 00:33:24,480
Are you hot?

915
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:25,330
No.

916
00:33:25,960 --> 00:33:27,740
Take it off. You'll get heatstroke.

917
00:33:27,740 --> 00:33:28,800
No, no. I'm not hot.

918
00:33:28,980 --> 00:33:30,040
Is there any water?

919
00:33:30,090 --> 00:33:30,820
Water?

920
00:33:30,980 --> 00:33:31,980
I want some water.

921
00:33:35,070 --> 00:33:36,400
Did we finish our water?

922
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:37,720
No water left?

923
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:39,420
-Forget it. It's fine.
-Let me buy you a bottle.

924
00:33:39,420 --> 00:33:39,940
It's fine.

925
00:33:39,940 --> 00:33:41,000
Really, it's fine.

926
00:33:41,110 --> 00:33:42,010
You look like you've been poisoned.

927
00:33:42,010 --> 00:33:44,670
-There will be water later.
-Put away the money.

928
00:33:59,460 --> 00:34:00,260
It's raining.

929
00:34:00,700 --> 00:34:01,550
It's raining!

930
00:34:09,500 --> 00:34:10,110
Boss.

931
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:11,320
Here, put this on.

932
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,290
Hurry, hurry. The clothes.

933
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:15,670
Okay.

934
00:34:20,730 --> 00:34:21,090
Done.

935
00:34:23,110 --> 00:34:24,480
I'll show you a magic trick.

936
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:25,340
Watch closely.

937
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:29,900
Come on.

938
00:34:30,750 --> 00:34:32,310
Raincoats!

939
00:34:32,550 --> 00:34:34,159
No extra charge in the rain!

940
00:34:34,260 --> 00:34:35,070
Over here!

941
00:34:35,150 --> 00:34:35,630
Over here!

942
00:34:35,630 --> 00:34:36,150
Come on!

943
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:37,840
Raincoats!

944
00:34:37,880 --> 00:34:39,360
No extra charge in the rain!

945
00:34:39,360 --> 00:34:40,159
One for me.

946
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:41,620
All kinds of styles

947
00:34:41,820 --> 00:34:43,139
and colors!

948
00:34:45,130 --> 00:34:45,820
One for me.

949
00:34:45,820 --> 00:34:47,280
Five yuan. Five yuan each.

950
00:34:47,980 --> 00:34:48,560
Here.

951
00:34:48,780 --> 00:34:49,389
Over here.

952
00:34:49,610 --> 00:34:50,210
Five yuan.

953
00:34:51,170 --> 00:34:52,090
Okay, thank you.

954
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:52,719
Thank you.

955
00:34:52,900 --> 00:34:53,280
Here.

956
00:34:54,010 --> 00:34:55,300
Come buy raincoats!

957
00:34:55,420 --> 00:34:55,940
Come on!

958
00:34:55,940 --> 00:34:56,710
Xu.

959
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:04,070
It's wet.

960
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:07,560
Pack our stuff up, quick.

961
00:35:07,650 --> 00:35:08,610
Pack all these clothes up.

962
00:35:08,610 --> 00:35:09,840
Pack them up. Put them inside.

963
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:10,170
Here.

964
00:35:19,650 --> 00:35:20,940
Xu.

965
00:35:21,010 --> 00:35:21,720
You two

966
00:35:21,980 --> 00:35:23,180
really came out on top

967
00:35:23,300 --> 00:35:24,430
on the street today.

968
00:35:24,780 --> 00:35:25,980
How much did you make?

969
00:35:26,650 --> 00:35:28,320
I haven't finished calculating yet.

970
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:29,090
Tell me now,

971
00:35:29,170 --> 00:35:31,030
how did you come up with this idea?

972
00:35:32,050 --> 00:35:33,170
It was a gift from above.

973
00:35:33,170 --> 00:35:35,090
Playing mysterious with me? Seriously.

974
00:35:35,090 --> 00:35:35,750
Spit it out.

975
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:38,000
The weather forecast.

976
00:35:38,460 --> 00:35:39,530
I checked the weather forecast.

977
00:35:39,530 --> 00:35:40,530
It said it's going to rain

978
00:35:40,530 --> 00:35:41,530
for the next few days.

979
00:35:41,530 --> 00:35:42,650
I remembered no one sold raincoats

980
00:35:42,650 --> 00:35:43,610
in this market.

981
00:35:43,860 --> 00:35:45,720
So I decided to stock some and try.

982
00:35:45,820 --> 00:35:47,550
Aren't you clever. Seriously.

983
00:35:48,170 --> 00:35:49,010
You made money.

984
00:35:49,010 --> 00:35:49,820
Shouldn't you treat me

985
00:35:49,820 --> 00:35:50,420
to a drink?

986
00:35:50,530 --> 00:35:51,130
Of course.

987
00:35:51,380 --> 00:35:52,300
I want something ice-cold.

988
00:35:52,300 --> 00:35:52,630
Okay.

989
00:35:52,730 --> 00:35:53,130
Great.

990
00:35:53,170 --> 00:35:53,940
Get one for Zhuang Zhuang too.

991
00:35:53,940 --> 00:35:54,710
For sure.

992
00:36:01,210 --> 00:36:01,780
Tell me.

993
00:36:03,170 --> 00:36:04,970
What's going on between you two?

994
00:36:05,650 --> 00:36:07,050
We're business partners.

995
00:36:07,050 --> 00:36:09,900
Business partners? Who are you kidding?

996
00:36:10,170 --> 00:36:11,050
It's true.

997
00:36:11,420 --> 00:36:12,630
I saw you two just now,

998
00:36:13,300 --> 00:36:14,690
working in the rain like that.

999
00:36:14,690 --> 00:36:15,260
My mind,

1000
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:16,280
whoosh, went straight back

1001
00:36:16,280 --> 00:36:17,400
to when I was young.

1002
00:36:18,590 --> 00:36:19,530
Speaking of back then,

1003
00:36:19,530 --> 00:36:21,050
I had so many guys chasing me too.

1004
00:36:21,050 --> 00:36:22,260
That was awesome.

1005
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:23,750
Really?

1006
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:25,460
Of course.

1007
00:36:25,550 --> 00:36:26,950
Go on and tell me about it.

1008
00:36:27,570 --> 00:36:29,360
Anyway, good men are scarce.

1009
00:36:29,460 --> 00:36:30,380
Grab him when you see one.

1010
00:36:30,380 --> 00:36:31,500
The next one might not be as good.

1011
00:36:31,500 --> 00:36:31,830
Here.

1012
00:36:31,900 --> 00:36:33,420
-You're so beautiful.
-It's chilled.

1013
00:36:33,420 --> 00:36:35,670
Open your eyes wide and take a good look.

1014
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:36,860
What are you talking about?

1015
00:36:36,860 --> 00:36:38,020
I'm saying you have big eyes.

1016
00:36:38,020 --> 00:36:39,080
My eyes aren't big.

1017
00:36:39,090 --> 00:36:40,330
Your eyes are.

1018
00:36:40,420 --> 00:36:40,950
I know.

1019
00:36:40,980 --> 00:36:42,510
That's why I was so popular.

1020
00:36:51,170 --> 00:36:53,030
Look at him, obsessed with money.

1021
00:36:58,610 --> 00:37:00,140
Finished calculating yet?

1022
00:37:02,730 --> 00:37:04,300
We made 250.

1023
00:37:05,650 --> 00:37:06,500
That much?

1024
00:37:06,650 --> 00:37:07,650
It suits you well.

1025
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:14,900
Boss,

1026
00:37:15,570 --> 00:37:17,000
Little Northeasterner snatched
a lot of customers

1027
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:18,860
at the train station again today.

1028
00:37:19,030 --> 00:37:20,480
The owners of the other hostels

1029
00:37:20,480 --> 00:37:21,840
have begged me several times.

1030
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:23,130
They want to buy you dinner

1031
00:37:23,130 --> 00:37:23,920
and discuss how to deal with

1032
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:25,550
this Little Northeasterner.

1033
00:37:25,550 --> 00:37:27,590
Do I look like I'm starving?

1034
00:37:28,230 --> 00:37:29,380
They buy me a meal,

1035
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:30,860
and I'll do their bidding?

1036
00:37:31,610 --> 00:37:32,670
Understood, Boss.

1037
00:37:33,090 --> 00:37:34,120
I'll go press them

1038
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:35,030
and see

1039
00:37:35,190 --> 00:37:36,820
just how sincere they really are.

1040
00:37:36,820 --> 00:37:37,710
Tell them,

1041
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:40,550
we are out here to make money.

1042
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:45,080
The greater the sincerity,
the bigger the job.

1043
00:37:45,710 --> 00:37:47,240
If they are sincere enough,

1044
00:37:47,590 --> 00:37:48,860
I can uproot Seasons Change

1045
00:37:48,860 --> 00:37:49,970
entirely.

1046
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:51,530
Let's go.

1047
00:37:51,650 --> 00:37:52,580
Take care, Boss.

1048
00:38:02,780 --> 00:38:04,380
Listen up!

1049
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:06,570
You all look like decent people

1050
00:38:06,570 --> 00:38:07,500
on the surface.

1051
00:38:07,500 --> 00:38:08,210
He's starting again.

1052
00:38:08,210 --> 00:38:08,830
But you act

1053
00:38:08,860 --> 00:38:10,130
with no manners!

1054
00:38:10,420 --> 00:38:12,020
Throwing trash everywhere.

1055
00:38:12,030 --> 00:38:12,610
You just don't

1056
00:38:12,610 --> 00:38:14,170
treat this place like your own home.

1057
00:38:14,170 --> 00:38:14,940
If you piss me off,

1058
00:38:14,940 --> 00:38:16,170
I'll kick you all out

1059
00:38:16,530 --> 00:38:17,860
to sleep on the streets.

1060
00:38:18,730 --> 00:38:20,300
Calm down.

1061
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:21,740
It's bad for your health.

1062
00:38:28,230 --> 00:38:29,490
You two went out to eat?

1063
00:38:30,980 --> 00:38:32,090
Didn't I tell you?

1064
00:38:33,010 --> 00:38:34,260
You need to be careful.

1065
00:38:34,260 --> 00:38:35,870
People will get jealous.

1066
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:36,890
Jealous of what?

1067
00:38:37,130 --> 00:38:38,340
We made money from doing business.

1068
00:38:38,340 --> 00:38:39,690
Can't we celebrate?

1069
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:42,090
I even brought you a dish.

1070
00:38:42,090 --> 00:38:43,420
Forget it. I'll have it.

1071
00:38:46,420 --> 00:38:48,350
I was saying that for your own good.

1072
00:38:49,610 --> 00:38:50,810
Those people inside,

1073
00:38:51,210 --> 00:38:52,340
looking all shifty,

1074
00:38:53,090 --> 00:38:54,160
are all tough nuts.

1075
00:38:54,260 --> 00:38:55,760
If I don't scold them every few days,

1076
00:38:55,760 --> 00:38:57,760
they'll turn the place upside down.

1077
00:38:58,940 --> 00:38:59,460
Mr. Xu,

1078
00:39:00,570 --> 00:39:02,230
I see you've fully recovered.

1079
00:39:02,860 --> 00:39:03,610
Don't take it to heart.

1080
00:39:03,610 --> 00:39:05,010
Don't lower yourself to their level.

1081
00:39:05,010 --> 00:39:05,870
How about this—

1082
00:39:06,340 --> 00:39:07,090
I'll switch you to a different room.

1083
00:39:07,090 --> 00:39:07,730
No need.

1084
00:39:08,730 --> 00:39:09,940
I'm digging my heels in.

1085
00:39:09,940 --> 00:39:10,870
I'm staying put.

1086
00:39:15,210 --> 00:39:16,610
I'm staying in that room.

1087
00:39:17,420 --> 00:39:18,200
Are you sure?

1088
00:39:18,820 --> 00:39:19,280
Well...

1089
00:39:20,510 --> 00:39:21,560
Mr. Xu,

1090
00:39:21,880 --> 00:39:23,940
just let me know if you need anything.

1091
00:39:30,550 --> 00:39:31,340
This liquor,

1092
00:39:32,420 --> 00:39:33,420
and these dishes—

1093
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:35,510
as Xu said,

1094
00:39:35,820 --> 00:39:38,230
he got these specially for us.

1095
00:39:41,460 --> 00:39:42,010
Here.

1096
00:39:44,570 --> 00:39:45,630
It's not poisoned.

1097
00:39:47,300 --> 00:39:48,230
Did you have any?

1098
00:39:50,090 --> 00:39:50,820
I had a bite

1099
00:39:51,610 --> 00:39:52,680
of everything.

1100
00:39:53,420 --> 00:39:54,420
Just a small bite.

1101
00:39:57,420 --> 00:39:59,170
He's being too nice for no reason.

1102
00:39:59,170 --> 00:40:00,500
He must be up to no good.

1103
00:40:00,650 --> 00:40:02,170
What are you talking about?

1104
00:40:02,170 --> 00:40:04,460
This is good food.

1105
00:40:04,650 --> 00:40:06,260
It's already been reheated once.

1106
00:40:06,260 --> 00:40:07,660
If we don't eat it now,

1107
00:40:07,780 --> 00:40:09,780
it won't taste good reheated again.

1108
00:40:10,340 --> 00:40:11,130
"Hoeing millet in the midday sun,

1109
00:40:11,130 --> 00:40:12,460
every grain is hard work."

1110
00:40:12,460 --> 00:40:13,660
If we throw this away,

1111
00:40:13,690 --> 00:40:14,940
it would be a real pity.

1112
00:40:14,940 --> 00:40:16,090
Corruption and waste

1113
00:40:16,090 --> 00:40:17,530
are the biggest crimes.

1114
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:18,860
Come on.

1115
00:40:24,420 --> 00:40:25,750
If you put it that way...

1116
00:40:25,940 --> 00:40:26,340
No.

1117
00:40:26,850 --> 00:40:27,930
What I mean is,

1118
00:40:29,300 --> 00:40:30,030
Zongbao

1119
00:40:30,170 --> 00:40:32,050
has already had a bite of everything.

1120
00:40:32,050 --> 00:40:33,160
We can't let him be
the only one compromised,

1121
00:40:33,160 --> 00:40:33,800
right?

1122
00:40:34,420 --> 00:40:35,720
If he eats and we don't,

1123
00:40:35,820 --> 00:40:37,310
it makes us look disloyal.

1124
00:40:37,530 --> 00:40:39,230
So you mean

1125
00:40:39,790 --> 00:40:41,450
we should share the blessings

1126
00:40:41,650 --> 00:40:42,760
and the burden?

1127
00:40:44,890 --> 00:40:46,050
Just eat.

1128
00:40:48,380 --> 00:40:49,180
Wait a second.

1129
00:40:49,610 --> 00:40:49,980
What?

1130
00:40:51,530 --> 00:40:52,620
Just like Zongbao,

1131
00:40:53,170 --> 00:40:54,970
we'll only take one bite of each.

1132
00:40:55,530 --> 00:40:55,860
Okay.

1133
00:41:02,420 --> 00:41:04,560
That bite is way too big.

1134
00:41:04,860 --> 00:41:06,920
It counts as a bite if I can stuff it in.

1135
00:41:07,130 --> 00:41:08,400
Don't waste it.

1136
00:41:08,460 --> 00:41:09,520
You're wasting it.

1137
00:41:16,690 --> 00:41:17,440
Oh my god.

1138
00:41:20,830 --> 00:41:21,170
You...

1139
00:41:21,170 --> 00:41:22,900
Why are you eating so much, too?

1140
00:41:22,900 --> 00:41:24,410
This is your second round.

1141
00:41:24,610 --> 00:41:25,860
That was just a taste test.

1142
00:41:25,860 --> 00:41:27,120
Now I'm really eating.

1143
00:41:30,500 --> 00:41:31,660
You two got

1144
00:41:31,690 --> 00:41:32,130
all the slices.

1145
00:41:32,130 --> 00:41:33,690
I'm only left with crumbs.

1146
00:41:48,700 --> 00:41:49,570
It's tasty.

1147
00:41:50,820 --> 00:41:51,350
Drink up.

1148
00:41:51,860 --> 00:41:52,330
Come on.

1149
00:42:01,570 --> 00:42:02,360
Cheers.

1150
00:42:04,010 --> 00:42:04,670
Don't move!

1151
00:42:19,360 --> 00:42:20,540
Is he delirious?

1152
00:42:20,630 --> 00:42:21,570
Or is he awake?

1153
00:42:24,480 --> 00:42:25,610
He's keeping score.

1154
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:33,600
You're awake?

1155
00:42:37,260 --> 00:42:38,320
Then the three of us

1156
00:42:39,210 --> 00:42:40,740
should get some more sleep.

1157
00:42:43,270 --> 00:42:45,140
I'll go drain my bladder first.

1158
00:42:52,840 --> 00:42:53,500
Is it good?
